    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="writingSession">
                <opener>
                    <dateline><pb/><hi rendition="#mPrint"> 79, Mosley Street,</hi></dateline>
                    <dateline>
                        <hi rendition="#mPrint">Manchester,</hi> Oct<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> 2<hi rendition="#sup">nd</hi>
                        <hi rendition="#mPrint">186</hi>7</dateline>
                    <salute><expan>D<ex>ea</ex>r</expan> Engells—</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I saw <persName key="ed_fcp_sxl_dhb">Murray</persName> the Horse Dealer on <seg type="comment"><orig>Saturday</orig><note xml:id="cf80aa48-21e6-42b7-8cde-7484d7f86157">28. September
                        1867.</note></seg> and asked him if he had anything like carrying 14 Stone
                    with hounds at about 70 £.—He seemd to think he had so I said I would probably
                    bring a friend to look at it.—The enclosed I received from <persName key="ed_adb_4f5_zgb">W. Henderson</persName> yesterday.—</p>
                <closer>Your <expan>tru<ex>ly</ex></expan><lb/>Joe Lomax <pb/></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
